== Features == Nishine Shrine enshrines two individuals, {{ill|Sato Shin'emon|ja|佐藤新右衛門|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sato Shin'emon|qq=}} and {{ill|Furukawa Zenbei|ja|古川善兵衛|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa Zenbei|qq=}}, who contributed significantly to the development of the {{ill|Nishine Irrigation Canal|ja|西根堰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishine Irrigation Canal|qq=}} during the early [[Edo period]]. The shrine was established in [[1887]] ([[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 20) by 4,231 farmers from 33 villages in Nishine to honor their contributions, which greatly benefited agriculture in the area. The autumn festival is held annually on [[September 14]]. The shrine grounds were previously the site of the [[:en:Kariya Domain|Kariya Domain]]'s encampment from [[1792]] ([[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 4) to the Meiji period. Stone monuments on the western side of the shrine commemorate Furukawa Zenbei's accomplishments, with some relocated from the vicinity of the Nishine Canal’s upper intake and other areas like the {{ill|Inariya Ryokan|ja|稲荷屋旅館|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inariya Ryokan|qq=}} in the [[:en:Iizaka Onsen|Iizaka Onsen]] district.
The grounds also house the '''Takahata Tenmangu''' (高畑天満宮), a shrine devoted to Tenjin worship, popularly known as the "Takahata Tenjin-sama." The shrine holds the {{ill|Uso-Kae Festival|ja|鷽替え|1=Uso-kae Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uso-Kae Festival|13=User:Immanuelle/Uso-kae Festival|qq=}} from January 13 to 16 and on April 27, attracting tens of thousands of visitors seeking blessings for good health and academic success. Wooden [[:en:Eurasian bullfinch|Uso]] figurines are sold during the festival for their protective charms.
== Annual Events == {| class="wikitable" |+ !Date !Event |- |January 1–3 |New Year's Visit (Hatsumode) |- |Mid-January |Nishine Shrine "Dondo Festival" Takahata Tenmangu "Uso-Kae Festival" |- |May 3 |Spring Grand Festival |- |September 14 |Autumn Grand Festival |- |December 23 |Year-End Market |}
== Prayer Services ==
=== In-Shrine Prayers === * Household safety * Prosperous business * Vehicle purification * Safe childbirth * First shrine visit for newborns * Yakubarai (purification from misfortune) * Directional avoidance * Shichi-Go-San festival prayers * Academic success * Recovery from illness
=== Off-Site Rituals === * Groundbreaking ceremonies * Building Completion tier 2]][[Category: ceremonies * Purification for renovations * Demolition purification
== Access == * A 9-minute walk from [[:en:Iizaka Onsen Station|Iizaka Onsen Station]] ({{OSM経路図|start=37.83045,140.45473|goal=37.83095,140.46043|name=Route Map}}).
== Related Articles == {{Commonscat}} * {{ill|Nishine Irrigation Canal|ja|西根堰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishine Irrigation Canal|qq=}}
